 South Africa has a total of 17 200 confirmed Covid-19 cases according to an announcement by minister of health, Dr Zweli Mkhize, on Tuesday, May 19. A total of 78 of those cases have been recorded in Mpumalanga. According to data released by the Mpumalanga Department of Health, 57 recoveries have been recorded to date. There have been no deaths recorded in Mpumalanga. • Bushbuckridge: 1 case and 1 recovery
• City of Mbombela: 17 cases and 8 recoveries
• Nkomazi: 20 cases and 20 recoveries
• Thaba Chweu: 2 cases and 1 recovery • Chief Albert Luthuli: 1 case
• Dipaliseng: 0 cases
• Dr Pixely Ka Isaka Seme: 17 cases and 15 recoveries
• Govan Mbeki: 4 cases and 2 recoveries
• Lekwa: 2 cases and 2 recoveries
• Mkhondo: 0 cases
